review_comments.body:
The amount of classes in DI Fakes is getting pretty large, consider just one generic class for all of these:

```
public class RoundAndRoundWeGo<TDependency> {
    public RoundAndRoundWeGo(TDependency obj) { }
}
```

Granted this introduces a slight variation of generics, and you lose the description in the class name (but the test name should be enough), for saves adding 7-8 more classes

